<subSubSection id="1C1C889AA99816F744195F964933DA91" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="type material">
<paragraph id="E85C0DB658B987ADB552DF8D42278846" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="403488C9A53798293C304F93AFE9649F" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="9B2F18DB05371271EE2E90B6B3F8F1A6" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Holotype</emphasis>
: ♂, Baoshan City, Mt Gaoligongshan, Yunnan Province, China (
<geoCoordinate id="D45B17D8905AC9DC64AADE2E461108AD" degrees="98" direction="east" minutes="47" orientation="longitude" precision="15" seconds="42" value="98.795">98°47'42&quot;E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="B6DC7B5E2A45C5AC47536F81C3C518DE" degrees="25" direction="north" minutes="18" orientation="latitude" precision="15" seconds="20" value="25.305555">25°18'20&quot;N</geoCoordinate>
; 1745 m elev.), 4 August 2018, coll. Zhou Yu (GUGC). 
<emphasis id="A9E522AA50DED48126E482D6D55D7B6B" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Paratypes</emphasis>
: 1♂, 6♀♀, same data as holotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4E00FF827BE574FE0E4F6ED83E22113C" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C4F492BD2AF5B1434BE5FF48EF1A9E35" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="49DC9393D3110D534579BE642CA9BBB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
The new species can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="B55144B542C9F70FE10CE1537310882E" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idioscopus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0804A4CFB8ABFB60F410AADFF26D48B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Idioscopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the following features: anal tube short; style apophysis with a row of three or four subapical teeth along inner margin; aedeagal shaft with long, recurved, hook-like apical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A38C59BB6465FB7A376389428ACB08B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph id="98246304C68D72ADD2721E5E5A8A1970" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="933579DC0F36EC27F120FF1C5E08E09E" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="C1D21FD422EBCCF130ADD4F0772760D4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="78BB257C8A5AC6FCB22F33387A1D9FB3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Coloration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Ground coloration translucent brown. Vertex pale brown with two round spots close to the adjacent eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="35BCFF60B7D9EEBF6E70C0AA2A95180B" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A</figureCitation>
). Eyes and ocelli brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="33C5253B18552AAF3C1E5510F3F60103" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A-C</figureCitation>
). Face (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="918FACFB6A4458A5823A7CA7AE8C1F07" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1B, C</figureCitation>
) yellowish white, narrow area along inner margin of eye, area surrounding bases of antennae, and inner margins of gena along frontal suture black, upper area with dark brown semicircular marking. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="80C42C6AD56720B32AEAFF868787E283" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown along anterior margin, posterior two-thirds brown, with a brown U-shaped band medially. Mesosternum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F1ECADAA066530000D0BA0D52DF94FBC" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A</figureCitation>
) black, mesepimeron with black spot. Mesonotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B7AD2BC121AF819DAD2546C2BB498A50" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A</figureCitation>
) yellow with pair of triangular, laterobasal, black maculae. Forewing with veins brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2A109DEBB9176E7DE8A6217C69D8E61F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="7A24B350E2812B88FAA9DBDB87912D5A" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="E8D71175100D78F9D88434A010B00EAF" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="28F5F3A092C5ED997BCC80B68AADF5BB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="1D3FE1FA5EEED3518F2E90EA133161CA" authorityName="Wang &amp; Wang &amp; Dai &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idioscopus bihamulus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bihamulus">
