<emphasis id="E1529BB06AC90D5253E26DE15D1D0E46" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">H</emphasis>
aedeagus, lateral view 
<emphasis id="2DC5667E60B3DB43FFF0ABAC4BF320AE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I</emphasis>
aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="1E9FBD20EE667B21D308C680DB91821C" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="8D4BBCFD5CB0B0F4EE4F344B82276BE7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="8D95C9D7AF14831E05DCF117FBAB44D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Male genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male pygofer (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="12649250368D2DF0006DE3A52DA04C31" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1E, F</figureCitation>
) without ventral process; anal collar thin with apex upturned; anterodorsal apodemes well developed. Anal tube (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F2FCD3B3CD5D5ABD1CD642D5E528E702" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1E</figureCitation>
) short. Subgenital plates (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="33A6B576516875A2A9FF84298C0BB35D" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1E</figureCitation>
) of uniform width, with reduced hair-like marginal setae. Connective (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4AB54E6D53067868589E68C115AD74AE" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1G</figureCitation>
) T-shaped, with stem narrow. Style apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="792D86AD16482432300A33A7D1188358" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1G</figureCitation>
) with a row of three or four tooth-like projections along inner margin subapically, outer margin with macrosetae in distal one-third. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="348A1293F5086ED439CAF14E819CA932" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671692" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">1H, I</figureCitation>
) with shaft laterally compressed, with pair of long, recurved, hook-like processes subapically from ventral margin, acute apically; basal apodeme pillar-like in lateral view, distally and laterally expanded in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D69B471E85FDC0409BCFD8D1BAC3BA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="75214BD1804695D56307A286C7E9D39B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis id="427B7A54D87F5B195C20C03A5A993A1E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Posterior margin of sternite VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DC18CF932A0FC5A08EA1E9C141EC00DB" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Ovipositor. Female. A-E Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. F-J Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. A, F sternite VII B, G first valvula C, H apex of first valvula D, I second valvula E, J apex of second valvula." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671694" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">3A</figureCitation>
) slightly produced medially. Valvulae as in Figure 
<figureCitation id="7D457EA170DFFD7311B94A6209D3C3AD" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Ovipositor. Female. A-E Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. F-J Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. A, F sternite VII B, G first valvula C, H apex of first valvula D, I second valvula E, J apex of second valvula." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671694" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">3B-E</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3714ABE0321DD1604F03DD89F1304A8D" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671694" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
