<subSubSection id="1D7DFBFFF9E20CA74997812796A8352C" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph id="7AD732CCDB86C94A1E7A23D346567539" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Measurements (mm).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D7D8072AEC29DFB6CCE2F021EE6E5FFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Male: body length including tegmina 3.70-3.80. Medial length of crown 0.13-0.16, width 1.25-1.30. Distance from ocellus to eyes 0.15-0.20. Medial length of pronotum 0.40-0.45, width 1.10-1.20; scutellum length 0.50-0.55, width 0.95-1.05. Female: body length including tegmina 3.70-3.90.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0472064D4F8762776AF67890AF121FB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4DB2575AC538F3BCD381210DAD52EDCC" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A1D45BE8B0D2FFC1AC41ED76E546E8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">The specific epithet refers to the two hamulus-like (hook-like) aedeagal processes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
